<span class="headers">Freeport Innoruuk INT Casters (Rage Sorceror) Armor</span>
<p>
<p>
The questgiver’s name is Marv Orilis and is located in East Freeport sewers among the Dismal Rage aligned guilds. <i>Please note that while the bracers are not lore, the bracer materials often are, so make your first bracer before you get the parts for a second one</i>
</p>
<p>
Class: Wizard, Magician, Enchanter, Necromancer. Race: Human. Deity: Innoruuk. Except for the wristbands, all armor and weapon is Lore, Magic & NO DROP. Here follows a transcript of the quest.
</p>
<p>
You say, 'Hail, Marv Orilis'
</p>
<p>
Marv Orilis says 'Yes? I am a very busy man. I assist new necromancers, wizards, magicians, and enchanters that have joined the Dismal Rage. Are you a sorcerer that has [recently joined] us?'
</p>
<p>
 You say, 'I have recently joined you'
</p>
<p>
 Marv Orilis says 'Then I welcome you to the path of rage. We sorcerers fulfill a crucial role within the Dismal Rage. Under the guidance of Opal Darkbriar, a founder of our order, we study the darkest aspects of the various sorcerous arts so that we may aid and bring power to others who follow our patron deity, Innoruuk, the Prince of Hate. If you desire I will help you obtain a suit of [protective clothing] suitable for a practitioner of the sorcerous arts. Once you have been properly outfitted, return to me and I will aid you in obtaining a [Staff of Dismal Rage].'
</p>
<p>
You say, 'I desire a suit of protective clothing'
</p>
<p>
 Marv Orilis says 'You will require this Curing Kit to craft your clothing and robe. The materials required vary depending on the article of clothing you desire to craft. Do you desire to craft a [rage sorcerer cap], [rage sorcerer wristband], [rage sorcerer gloves], [rage sorcerer boots], [rage sorcerer sleeves], [rage sorcerer pantaloons], or [rage sorcerer robe]?'
</p>
<p>
You say, 'I want to craft a rage sorcerer cap'
</p>
<p>
 Marv Orilis says 'To craft a Rage Sorcerer Cap you will require two [silk thread], gilla monster hatchling bile, and a young gilla monster skin. Once you have the necessary components combine them in your Curing Kit with this Tattered Cap Pattern.'
</p>
<blockquote>
<p>
Rage Sorcerer Cap.<br />
 (AC: +2 Int: +1 HP: +3).<br />
 2 Silk Thread (combine 2 spiderling silk in a Loom or a Tailoring Kit to get 1 Silk Thread).<br />
 1 gilla monster hatchling bile.<br />
 1 young gilla monster skin.
</p>
</blockquote>
<p>
You say, 'i wish to craft a rage sorcerer wristband'
</p>
<p>
 Marv Orilis says 'To craft a Rage Sorcerer Wristband you require a [silk thread], gilla monster hatchling bile, and a rattlesnake skin. Once you have the necessary components combine them in your Curing Kit with this Tattered Wristband Pattern.'
</p>
<blockquote>
<p>
Rage Sorcerer Bracer. (note: not the same name that is given by Marv Orilis).<br />
 AC: +1 Int: +1 Mana: +2<br />
 1 Silk Thread.<br />
 1 gilla monster hatchling bile.<br />
 1 rattlesnake skin.
</p>
</blockquote>
<p>
You say, 'i want to craft a rage sorcerer gloves'
</p>
<p>
 Marv Orilis says 'To craft Rage Sorcerer Gloves you require two [silk thread], gilla monster hatchling bile, two desert spiderling hairs, and a young gilla monster skin. Once you have the necessary components combine them in your Curing Kit with this Tattered Glove Pattern.'
</p>
<blockquote>
<p>
Rage Sorcerer Gloves.<br />
 Stats unknown.<br />
 2 Silk Threads.<br />
 1 gilla monster hatchling bile.<br />
 2 desert spiderling hairs.<br />
 1 young gilla monster skin.
</p>
</blockquote>
<p>
You say, 'I want to craft a rage sorcerer boots'
</p>
<p>
 [Wed Jul 31 20:40:05 2002] Marv Orilis says 'To craft Rage Sorcerer Boots you require two [silk thread], gilla monster hatchling bile, and two ruined coyote pelts. Once you have the necessary components combine them in your Curing Kit with this Tattered Boot Pattern.'
</p>
<blockquote>
<p>
Rage Sorcerer Boots.<br />
 Stats unknown.<br />
 2 Silk Threads.<br />
 1 gilla monster hatchling bile.<br />
 2 ruined coyote pelts.
</p>
</blockquote>
<p>
You say, 'i want to craft rage sorcerer sleeves'
</p>
<p>
 Marv Orilis says 'To craft Rage Sorcerer Sleeves you require two [silk thread], young gilla monster bile, and two young gilla monster skins. Once you have the necessary components combine them in your Curing Kit with this Tattered Sleeves Pattern.'
</p>
<blockquote>
<p>
Rage Sorcerer Sleeves.<br />
 AC: +3 Int: +2 HP: +3<br />
 2 Silk Threads.<br />
 1 young gilla monster bile.<br />
 2 young gilla monster skins.
</p>
</blockquote>
<p>
You say, 'i want to craft rage sorcerer pantaloons'
</p>
<p>
 Marv Orilis says 'To craft Rage Sorcerer Pantaloons you require two [silk thread], young gilla monster bile, and four young gilla monster skins. Once you have the necessary components combine them in your Curing Kit with this Tattered Leggings Pattern.'
</p>
<blockquote>
<p>
Rage Sorcerer Pantaloons.<br />
 Stats unknown.<br />
 2 Silk Threads.<br />
 1 young gilla monster bile.<br />
 4 young gilla monster skins.
</p>
</blockquote>
<p>
You say, 'i want to craft a rage sorcerer robe'
</p>
<p>
 Marv Orilis says 'To craft a Rage Sorcerer Robe you will require three [silk thread], gilla monster bile, two gilla monster skins, and a desert tarantula hairs. Once you have the necessary components combine them in your Curing Kit with this Tattered Robe Pattern.'
</p>
<blockquote>
<p>
Rage Sorcerer Robe.<br />
 Stats unknown.<br />
 3 Silk Threads.<br />
 1 gilla monster bile.<br />
 2 gilla monster skins.<br />
 1 desert tarantula hairs.
</p>
</blockquote>
<p>
And the Weapon.
</p>
<p>
You say, 'What staff of dismal rage'
</p>
<p>
 Marv Orilis says 'The Dismal Rage has many enemies still here in Freeport that would uncover us and see us destroyed. Lately a wizard of the Arcane Scientists, Yovik Splegle, has been asking questions about Opal Darkbriar. Find this inquisitive wizard and silence him for good. When you have completed the task return to me with the wizards head.'
</p>
<blockquote>
<p>
Staff of dismal rage.<br />
 Two Hand Blunt<br />
 Damage: 7<br />
 Delay: 37<br />
 Classes: Wizard Magician Enchanter Necromancer.<br />
 Races: Human.<br />
 Deity: Innoruuk.
</p>
</blockquote></p><p>
